"]},{"name":"TOTAL_CREDITS","sample_values":["0.005736388889","0.0008256470693","0.01914450292"]},{"name":"TOTAL_ELAPSED_TIME_SEC","sample_values":["5.47","0.641","927.292"]}],"time_dimensions":[{"name":"CAPTURE_TIMESTAMP","sample_values":["2026-03-18T20:06:03.400+0000","2026-03-17T21:19:54.080+0000","2026-03-17T23:19:55.247+0000"]},{"name":"QUERY_DATE","sample_values":["2026-03-15","2026-03-16","2026-03-13"]}]},{"name":"QUERY_ANALYSIS_RESULTS_IT","dimensions":[{"name":"ANALYSIS_ID","sample_values":["6","1","4"]},{"name":"CAPTURE_ID","sample_values":["38","2","3"]},{"name":"KEY_FINDINGS","sample_values":[" - Cache Hit: 0%\\n- Partitions Scanned: 0%"," - Cache Hit: 0%\\n- Partitions Scanned: 100%"," - Cache Hit: 1%\\n- Partitions Scanned: 100%"]},{"name":"OPTIMIZATION_SUGGESTIONS","sample_values":["1. **Increase Warehouse Size**: The current warehouse size is X-Small. Increase it to a larger size (e.g., Small or Medium) to provide more compute resources and reduce query execution time.\\n\\n2. **Reduce Data Generation**: The query generates a large amount of data (1 trillion rows). Reduce the ROWCOUNT in the GENERATOR functions to a more manageable number to decrease the data volume and cost.\\n\\n3. **Use Result Caching**: To improve cache hit rate, use the RESULT_SCAN function to cache the query results for subsequent reuse, reducing the need to recompute the data.","1. **Increase Cache Hit Rate**:\\n   - **Action**: Implement result caching for frequently run queries to increase the cache hit rate.\\n   - **Command**: `ALTER SESSION SET USE_CACHED_RESULT = TRUE;`\\n\\n2. **Optimize Warehouse Size**:\\n   - **Action**: Increase the warehouse size to improve query performance and reduce execution time.\\n   - **Command**: `ALTER WAREHOUSE <warehouse_name> SET SIZE = ''SMALL'';`\\n\\n3. **Reduce Data Scanned**:\\n   - **Action**: Use clustering keys and partitioning to reduce the amount of data scanned.\\n   - **Command**:\\n     ```sql\\n     CREATE OR REPLACE TABLE <table_name>\\n     CLUSTER BY (<clustering_key>);\\n     ```\\n     ```sql\\n     ALTER TABLE <table_name>\\n     ADD PARTITION BY (<partition_key>);\\n     ```","1. **Reduce Data Scanned**: Limit the columns selected to only those needed instead of using `SELECT *`.\\n   ```sql\\n   SELECT SCHEDULED_TIME, TASK_NAME, STATE FROM TABLE(QUERY_OPTIMIZATION_DB.INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TASK_HISTORY(\\n       TASK_NAME => ''COLLECT_BAD_QUERIES_TASK'',\\n       SCHEDULED_TIME_RANGE_START => DATEADD(DAY, -1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP())\\n   )) ORDER BY SCHEDULED_TIME DESC\\n   ```\\n\\n2. **Optimize Warehouse Size**: Consider using a larger warehouse size if the query is taking longer than expected.\\n   ```sql\\n   USE WAREHOUSE MEDIUM;\\n   ```\\n\\n3. **Leverage Caching**: If the query is run frequently, consider using result caching to reduce the cost and improve performance.\\n   ```sql\\n   ALTER SESSION SET USE_CACHED_RESULT = TRUE;\\n   ```"]},{"name":"QUERY_ID","sample_values":["01c3019d-0001-9c5d-0002-724e0015f6a6","01c30165-0001-9c47-0002-724e00161072","01c30165-0001-9c47-0002-724e0016106e"]},{"name":"SUGGESTED_QUERY_REWRITE","sample_values":[" ```sql\\nINSERT INTO QUERY_OPTIMIZATION_DB.AGENT.QUERY_ANALYSIS_RESULTS (\\n    CAPTURE_ID, QUERY_ID, KEY_FINDINGS, OPTIMIZATION_SUGGESTIONS, SUGGESTED_QUERY_REWRITE\\n)\\nSELECT\\n    b.CAPTURE_ID,\\n    b.QUERY_ID,\\n\\n    SNOWFLAKE.CORTEX.COMPLETE(\\n        ''mistral-large2'',\\n        CONCAT(\\n            ''You are a Snowflake performance expert. Identify performance issues in 2-3 bullet points. Be concise.\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Status: '', b.EXECUTION_STATUS, ''\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Cost: $'', ROUND(b.TOTAL_COST_USD, 2)::VARCHAR, ''\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Runtime: '', ROUND(b.TOTAL_ELAPSED_TIME_SEC/60, 1)::VARCHAR, '' min\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Data Scanned: '', ROUND(b.GB_SCANNED, 1)::VARCHAR, '' GB\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Cache Hit: '', ROUND(b.PERCENTAGE_SCANNED_FROM_CACHE, 1)::VARCHAR, ''%\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Partitions Scanned: '', ROUND(b.PARTITION_SCAN_PCT, 1)::VARCHAR, ''%\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Spill: '', b.SPILL_STATUS, ''\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Warehouse: '', COALESCE(b.WAREHOUSE_SIZE, ''Unknown''), ''\\\\n'',\\n            ''List ONLY the issues found.''\\n        )\\n    ) AS KEY_FINDINGS,\\n\\n    SNOWFLAKE.CORTEX.COMPLETE(\\n        ''mistral-large2'',\\n        CONCAT(\\n            ''You are a Snowflake optimization expert. Provide 2-3 actionable fixes. Be concise.\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Type: '', b.QUERY_TYPE, ''\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Cost: $'', ROUND(b.TOTAL_COST_USD, 2)::VARCHAR, ''\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Data Scanned: '', ROUND(b.GB_SCANNED, 1)::VARCHAR, '' GB\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Cache Hit: '', ROUND(b.PERCENTAGE_SCANNED_FROM_CACHE, 1)::VARCHAR, ''%\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Partitions Scanned: '', ROUND(b.PARTITION_SCAN_PCT, 1)::VARCHAR, ''%\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Spill: '', b.SPILL_STATUS, ''\\\\n'',\\n            ''- Warehouse: '', COALESCE(b.WAREHOUSE_SIZE, ''Unknown''), ''\\\\n'',\\n            ''Provide ONLY the optimized SQL query. Consider:\\\\n'',\\n            ''1. Add appropriate WHERE clauses for partition pruning\\\\n'',\\n            ''2. Use clustering keys if applicable\\\\n'',\\n            ''3. Limit columns in SELECT\\\\n'',\\n            ''4. Add LIMIT if possible\\\\n'',\\n            ''5. Optimize JOINs\\\\n'',\\n            ''Return ONLY the optimized SQL, no explanation.''\\n        )\\n    ) AS OPTIMIZATION_SUGGESTIONS,\\n\\n    SNOWFLAKE.CORTEX.COMPLETE(\\n        ''mistral-large2'',\\n        CONCAT(\\n            ''You are a Snowflake optimization expert. Provide the optimized SQL query. Consider:\\\\n'',\\n            ''1. Add appropriate WHERE clauses for partition pruning\\\\n'',\\n            ''2. Use clustering keys if applicable\\\\n'',\\n            ''3. Limit columns in SELECT\\\\n'',\\n            ''4. Add LIMIT if possible\\\\n'',\\n            ''5. Optimize JOINs\\\\n'',\\n            ''Return ONLY the optimized SQL, no explanation.''\\n        )\\n    ) AS SUGGESTED_QUERY_REWRITE\\n\\nFROM QUERY_OPTIMIZATION_DB.AGENT.QUERY_ANALYSIS_RESULTS b\\nWHERE b.EXECUTION_STATUS = ''SUCCESS''\\nAND b.GB_SCANNED > 0\\nAND b.PARTITION_SCAN_PCT < 100\\nLIMIT 100;\\n```"," ```sql\\nSELECT\\n    SCHEDULED_TIME,\\n    STATE,\\n    QUERY_ID,\\n    NAME\\nFROM\\n    TABLE(QUERY_OPTIMIZATION_DB.INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TASK_HISTORY(\\n        TASK_NAME => ''COLLECT_BAD_QUERIES_TASK'',\\n        SCHEDULED_TIME_RANGE_START => DATEADD(DAY, -1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP())\\n    ))\\nWHERE\\n    SCHEDULED_TIME >= DATEADD(DAY, -1, CURRENT_TIMESTAMP())\\nORDER BY\\n    SCHEDULED_TIME DESC\\nLIMIT 100;\\n```"," ```sql\\nWITH results AS (\\n    SELECT\\n        $1,\\n        $2\\n    FROM TABLE(RESULT_SCAN(''01c30165-0001-9c0d-0002-724e00162046''))\\n),\\nstats AS (\\n    SELECT\\n        COUNT($1) AS count_1,\\n        MIN($1) AS min_1,\\n        MAX($1) AS max_1,\\n        SUM($1) AS sum_1,\\n        AVG($1) AS avg_1,\\n        COUNT($2) AS count_2,\\n        MIN($2) AS min_2,\\n        MAX($2) AS max_2,\\n        SUM($2) AS sum_2,\\n        AVG($2) AS avg_2\\n    FROM results\\n),\\nbuckets1 AS (\\n    SELECT\\n        CASE\\n            WHEN stats.min_1 = stats.max_1 THEN 1\\n            ELSE WIDTH_BUCKET(results.$1, stats.min_1, stats.max_1 + 1, 10)\\n        END AS b,\\n        COUNT(*) AS c\\n    FROM results\\n    JOIN stats ON 1=1\\n    GROUP BY b\\n),\\nstats1 AS (\\n    SELECT OBJECT_AGG(b, c) AS bucket_stats_1\\n    FROM buckets1\\n),\\nbuckets2 AS (\\n    SELECT\\n        CASE\\n            WHEN stats.min_2 = stats.max_2 THEN 1\\n            ELSE WIDTH_BUCKET(results.$2, stats.min_2, stats.max_2 + 1, 10)\\n        END AS b,\\n        COUNT(*) AS c\\n    FROM results\\n    JOIN stats ON 1=1\\n    GROUP BY b\\n),\\nstats2 AS (\\n    SELECT OBJECT_AGG(b, c) AS bucket_stats_2\\n    FROM buckets2\\n)\\nSELECT\\n    stats.count_1,\\n    stats.min_1,\\n    stats.max_1,\\n    stats.sum_1,\\n    stats.avg_1,\\n    stats.count_2,\\n    stats.min_2,\\n    stats.max_2,\\n    stats.sum_2,\\n    stats.avg_2,\\n    stats1.bucket_stats_1,\\n    stats2.bucket_stats_2\\nFROM stats, stats1, stats2\\nLIMIT 1;\\n```"]}],"time_dimensions":[{"name":"ANALYSIS_TIMESTAMP","sample_values":["2026-03-18T06:00:01.784+0000","2026-03-18T20:07:55.110+0000","2026-03-17T21:21:38.213+0000"]}]}],"relationships":[{"name":"BAD_QUERIES_RAW_IT_TO_QUERY_ANALYSIS_RESULTS_IT","join_type":"inner"}]}');
